{"type":"message","id":"557d696a","parentId":"b6b821fe","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:48:10.307Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"4204d642546b43d6aaa52b59de8916a0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Service: systemd user (enabled)\nFile logs: /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-06-03.log\nCommand: /root/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin/node /root/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/index.js gateway --port 18789\nService file: ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-gateway.service\nService env: OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789\n\nService config looks out of date or non-standard.\nService config issue: Gateway service PATH includes version managers or package managers; recommend a minimal PATH. (/root/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin, /root/.nvm/current/bin)\nService config issue: Gateway service uses Node from a version manager; it can break after upgrades. (/root/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin/node)\nRecommendation: run \"openclaw doctor\" (or \"openclaw doctor --repair\").\nConfig (cli): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nConfig (service): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\nGateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=18789 (service args)\nProbe target: ws://127.0.0.1:18789\nDashboard: http://127.0.0.1:18789/\nProbe note: Loopback-only gateway; only local clients can connect.\n\nCLI version: 2026.5.18 (~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin/openclaw)\nGateway version: 2026.5.18"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3570,"aggregated":"Service: systemd user (enabled)\nFile logs: /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-06-03.log\nCommand: /root/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin/node /root/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/index.js gateway --port 18789\nService file: ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-gateway.service\nService env: OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789\n\nService config looks out of date or non-standard.\nService config issue: Gateway service PATH includes version managers or package managers; recommend a minimal PATH. (/root/